<span id="v.iv.lvii-p2"></span><span class="c12"><span
id="v.iv.lvii-p2.1"></span>Theodotus, <span
id="fr_2667"></span>[2668](#fn_2667.md) </span> <span
id="fr_2668"></span>[2669](#fn_2668.md) bishop of Ancyra in Galatia, while
at <span id="fr_2669"></span>[2670](#fn_2669.md) Ephesus, wrote against
Nestorius a work of defence and refutation, <span
id="fr_2670"></span>[2671](#fn_2670.md) written, to be sure, in dialectic
style, but interwoven with passages from the Holy Scriptures. His method
was to make statements and then quote proof texts from the Scriptures.

